 441 def merge_v2_checkpoints(checkpoint_prefixes, destination_prefix, delete_old_dirs=True, name=None):
 442   r"""V2 format specific: merges the metadata files of sharded checkpoints.  The
 443 
 444   result is one logical checkpoint, with one physical metadata file and renamed
 445   data files.
 446 
 447   Intended for "grouping" multiple checkpoints in a sharded checkpoint setup.
 448 
 449   If delete_old_dirs is true, attempts to delete recursively the dirname of each
 450   path in the input checkpoint_prefixes.  This is useful when those paths are non
 451   user-facing temporary locations.
 452 
 453   Args:
 454     checkpoint_prefixes: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
 455       prefixes of V2 checkpoints to merge.
 456     destination_prefix: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
 457       scalar.  The desired final prefix.  Allowed to be the same
 458       as one of the checkpoint_prefixes.
 459     delete_old_dirs: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `True`. see above.
 460     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 461 
 462   Returns:
 463     The created Operation.
 464   """
 465   _ctx = _context._context
 466   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
 467     if delete_old_dirs is None:
 468       delete_old_dirs = True
 469     delete_old_dirs = _execute.make_bool(delete_old_dirs, "delete_old_dirs")
 470     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
 471         "MergeV2Checkpoints", checkpoint_prefixes=checkpoint_prefixes,
 472         destination_prefix=destination_prefix,
 473         delete_old_dirs=delete_old_dirs, name=name)
 474     return _op
 475     _result = None
 476     return _result
 477 
 478   else:
 479     try:
 480       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
 481         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
 482         "MergeV2Checkpoints", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks,
 483         checkpoint_prefixes, destination_prefix, "delete_old_dirs",
 484         delete_old_dirs)
 485       return _result
 486     except _core._FallbackException:
 487       return merge_v2_checkpoints_eager_fallback(
 488           checkpoint_prefixes, destination_prefix,
 489           delete_old_dirs=delete_old_dirs, name=name, ctx=_ctx)
 490     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
 491       if name is not None:
 492         message = e.message + " name: " + name
 493       else:
 494         message = e.message
 495       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)

 511                              attrs=_attrs, ctx=_ctx, name=name)

1061 def reader_restore_state(reader_handle, state, name=None):
1062   r"""Restore a reader to a previously saved state.
1063 
1064   Not all Readers support being restored, so this can produce an
1065   Unimplemented error.
1066 
1067   Args:
1068     reader_handle: A `Tensor` of type mutable `string`. Handle to a Reader.
1069     state: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1070       Result of a ReaderSerializeState of a Reader with type
1071       matching reader_handle.
1072     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1073 
1074   Returns:
1075     The created Operation.

1241 def restore(file_pattern, tensor_name, dt, preferred_shard=-1, name=None):
1242   r"""Restores a tensor from checkpoint files.
1243 
1244   Reads a tensor stored in one or several files. If there are several files (for
1245   instance because a tensor was saved as slices), `file_pattern` may contain
1246   wildcard symbols (`*` and `?`) in the filename portion only, not in the
1247   directory portion.
1248 
1249   If a `file_pattern` matches several files, `preferred_shard` can be used to hint
1250   in which file the requested tensor is likely to be found. This op will first
1251   open the file at index `preferred_shard` in the list of matching files and try
1252   to restore tensors from that file.  Only if some tensors or tensor slices are
1253   not found in that first file, then the Op opens all the files. Setting
1254   `preferred_shard` to match the value passed as the `shard` input
1255   of a matching `Save` Op may speed up Restore.  This attribute only affects
1256   performance, not correctness.  The default value -1 means files are processed in
1257   order.
1258 
1259   See also `RestoreSlice`.
1260 
1261   Args:
1262     file_pattern: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1263       Must have a single element. The pattern of the files from
1264       which we read the tensor.
1265     tensor_name: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1266       Must have a single element. The name of the tensor to be
1267       restored.
1268     dt: A `tf.DType`. The type of the tensor to be restored.
1269     preferred_shard: An optional `int`. Defaults to `-1`.
1270       Index of file to open first if multiple files match
1271       `file_pattern`.
1272     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1273 
1274   Returns:
1275     A `Tensor` of type `dt`.
1276   """
1277   _ctx = _context._context
1278   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1279     dt = _execute.make_type(dt, "dt")
1280     if preferred_shard is None:
1281       preferred_shard = -1
1282     preferred_shard = _execute.make_int(preferred_shard, "preferred_shard")
1283     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1284         "Restore", file_pattern=file_pattern, tensor_name=tensor_name, dt=dt,
1285         preferred_shard=preferred_shard, name=name)
1286     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1287     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1288     _attrs = ("dt", _op.get_attr("dt"), "preferred_shard",
1289               _op.get_attr("preferred_shard"))
1290     _execute.record_gradient(
1291       "Restore", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1292     _result, = _result
1293     return _result
1294 
1295   else:
1296     try:
1297       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1298         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name, "Restore",
1299         name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, file_pattern, tensor_name, "dt",
1300         dt, "preferred_shard", preferred_shard)
1301       return _result
1302     except _core._FallbackException:
1303       return restore_eager_fallback(
1304           file_pattern, tensor_name, dt=dt, preferred_shard=preferred_shard,
1305           name=name, ctx=_ctx)
1306     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
1307       if name is not None:
1308         message = e.message + " name: " + name
1309       else:
1310         message = e.message
1311       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)
1312

1315   r"""This is the slowpath function for Eager mode.
1316   This is for function restore
1317   """
1318   _ctx = ctx if ctx else _context.context()

1424 def restore_v2(prefix, tensor_names, shape_and_slices, dtypes, name=None):
1425   r"""Restores tensors from a V2 checkpoint.
1426 
1427   For backward compatibility with the V1 format, this Op currently allows
1428   restoring from a V1 checkpoint as well:
1429     - This Op first attempts to find the V2 index file pointed to by "prefix", and
1430       if found proceed to read it as a V2 checkpoint;
1431     - Otherwise the V1 read path is invoked.
1432   Relying on this behavior is not recommended, as the ability to fall back to read
1433   V1 might be deprecated and eventually removed.
1434 
1435   By default, restores the named tensors in full.  If the caller wishes to restore
1436   specific slices of stored tensors, "shape_and_slices" should be non-empty
1437   strings and correspondingly well-formed.
1438 
1439   Callers must ensure all the named tensors are indeed stored in the checkpoint.
1440 
1441   Args:
1442     prefix: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1443       Must have a single element.  The prefix of a V2 checkpoint.
1444     tensor_names: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1445       shape {N}.  The names of the tensors to be restored.
1446     shape_and_slices: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1447       shape {N}.  The slice specs of the tensors to be restored.
1448       Empty strings indicate that they are non-partitioned tensors.
1449     dtypes: A list of `tf.DTypes` that has length `>= 1`.
1450       shape {N}.  The list of expected dtype for the tensors.  Must match
1451       those stored in the checkpoint.
1452     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1453 
1454   Returns:
1455     A list of `Tensor` objects of type `dtypes`.
1456   """
1457   _ctx = _context._context
1458   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1459     if not isinstance(dtypes, (list, tuple)):
1460       raise TypeError(
1461           "Expected list for 'dtypes' argument to "
1462           "'restore_v2' Op, not %r." % dtypes)
1463     dtypes = [_execute.make_type(_t, "dtypes") for _t in dtypes]
1464     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1465         "RestoreV2", prefix=prefix, tensor_names=tensor_names,
1466         shape_and_slices=shape_and_slices, dtypes=dtypes, name=name)
1467     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1468     if not _result:
1469       return _op
1470     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1471     _attrs = ("dtypes", _op.get_attr("dtypes"))
1472     _execute.record_gradient(
1473       "RestoreV2", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1474     return _result
1475 
1476   else:
1477     try:
1478       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1479         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name, "RestoreV2",
1480         name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, prefix, tensor_names,
1481         shape_and_slices, "dtypes", dtypes)
1482       return _result
1483     except _core._FallbackException:
1484       return restore_v2_eager_fallback(
1485           prefix, tensor_names, shape_and_slices, dtypes=dtypes, name=name,
1486           ctx=_ctx)
1487     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
1488       if name is not None:
1489         message = e.message + " name: " + name
1490       else:
1491         message = e.message
1492       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)
1493

1496   r"""This is the slowpath function for Eager mode.

1547     try:
1548       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(

1550         _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, filename, tensor_names, data)
1551       return _result

1554           filename, tensor_names, data, name=name, ctx=_ctx)

1558       else:

1565   This is for function save

1579 def save_slices(filename, tensor_names, shapes_and_slices, data, name=None):
1580   r"""Saves input tensors slices to disk.
1581 
1582   This is like `Save` except that tensors can be listed in the saved file as being
1583   a slice of a larger tensor.  `shapes_and_slices` specifies the shape of the
1584   larger tensor and the slice that this tensor covers. `shapes_and_slices` must
1585   have as many elements as `tensor_names`.
1586 
1587   Elements of the `shapes_and_slices` input must either be:
1588 
1589   *  The empty string, in which case the corresponding tensor is
1590      saved normally.
1591   *  A string of the form `dim0 dim1 ... dimN-1 slice-spec` where the
1592      `dimI` are the dimensions of the larger tensor and `slice-spec`
1593      specifies what part is covered by the tensor to save.
1594 
1595   `slice-spec` itself is a `:`-separated list: `slice0:slice1:...:sliceN-1`
1596   where each `sliceI` is either:
1597 
1598   *  The string `-` meaning that the slice covers all indices of this dimension
1599   *  `start,length` where `start` and `length` are integers.  In that
1600      case the slice covers `length` indices starting at `start`.
1601 
1602   See also `Save`.
1603 
1604   Args:
1605     filename: A `Tensor` of type `string`.

1624     return _op

1626     return _result

1664 def save_v2(prefix, tensor_names, shape_and_slices, tensors, name=None):
1665   r"""Saves tensors in V2 checkpoint format.
1666 
1667   By default, saves the named tensors in full.  If the caller wishes to save
1668   specific slices of full tensors, "shape_and_slices" should be non-empty strings
1669   and correspondingly well-formed.
1670 
1671   Args:
1672     prefix: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1673       Must have a single element. The prefix of the V2 checkpoint to which we
1674       write the tensors.
1675     tensor_names: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1676       shape {N}. The names of the tensors to be saved.
1677     shape_and_slices: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1678       shape {N}.  The slice specs of the tensors to be saved.
1679       Empty strings indicate that they are non-partitioned tensors.
1680     tensors: A list of `Tensor` objects. `N` tensors to save.
1681     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1682 
1683   Returns:
1684     The created Operation.
1685   """
1686   _ctx = _context._context
1687   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1688     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1689         "SaveV2", prefix=prefix, tensor_names=tensor_names,
1690         shape_and_slices=shape_and_slices, tensors=tensors, name=name)
1691     return _op
1692     _result = None
1693     return _result
1694 
1695   else:
1696     try:
1697       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1698         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name, "SaveV2", name,
1699         _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, prefix, tensor_names,
1700         shape_and_slices, tensors)
1701       return _result
1702     except _core._FallbackException:
1703       return save_v2_eager_fallback(
1704           prefix, tensor_names, shape_and_slices, tensors, name=name,
1705           ctx=_ctx)
1706     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
1707       if name is not None:
1708         message = e.message + " name: " + name
1709       else:
1710         message = e.message
1711       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)
